rnational Airport (ORD)ChicagoUnited States24 min16 miChicago Midway International Airport (MDW)ChicagoUnited States22 min9 miMilwaukee Mitchell International Airport (MKE)MilwaukeeUnited States1 hr 22 min75 miIndianapolis International Airport (IND)IndianapolisUnited States2 hr 55 min165 miFrequently asked questions about flying from San Francisco to Chicago  How long does it take to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?4 hr is the shortest flight time from San Francisco to Chicago.When are the cheapest days to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?The cheapest days to fly are usually in  September. Typical prices range from $125 to $200.Which airlines provide the cheapest flights from San Francisco to Chicago?The best round-trip deal recently found on Google Flights from San Francisco to Chicago was with United from $179. The best one-way deal was with Alaska from $90.Some of the cheapest round-trip deals we found with different airlines:The cheapest United round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $179, flying from Aug 7 to Aug 13.The cheapest American round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $179, flying from Aug 8 to Aug 14.The cheapest Southwest round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $199, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 27.The cheapest Delta round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $257, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 29.The cheapest Alaska round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $188, flying from Aug 9 to Aug 15.The cheapest Frontier round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $238, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 27.What is the best airline to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?What counts as the best airline for your flights from San Francisco  to Chicago really depends on your individual needs.  You may have a favorite carrier or a loyalty program you like, but price, convenience, and airports served also come into play. Flexibility and booking terms – Can you change flights if you want to stay longer or get a refund if you have to postpone your trip? – are also factors that help determine which airline is best to fly from San Francisco  to Chicago.In terms of nonstop flights, United is the most popular. United offers 72 nonstop flights and 597 connecting flights per week. United flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).In terms of flights, Southwest is the most popular. Southwest offers 7 nonstop flights and 1,922 connecting flights per week. Southwest flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).Other popular airlines flying from San Francisco to Chicago are:American offers 41 nonstop flights and 233 connecting flights per week. American flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).Delta offers 543 connecting flights per week. Delta flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).Alaska offers 7 nonstop flights and 55 connecting flights per week. Alaska flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).Frontier offers 56 connecting flights per week. Frontier flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O\'Hare International Airport (ORD).The number of connecting flights refers to distinct flights with at least one stop between San Francisco  and Chicago.When are direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago available?There are direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago on a daily basis.Which airlines have direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago?Southwest, United, American and Alaska fly direct from San Francisco to Chicago.There are 72 United direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago per week. Flights are available every day.There are 41 American direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago per week. Flights are available every day.There are 7 Southwest direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago per week. Flights are available every day.There are 7 Alaska direct flights from San Francisco to Chicago per week. Flights are available every day.Use the Stops filter while searching for flights, to see only nonstop options in your results.What are the cheapest flights from San Francisco to Chicago?The cheapest round-trip flight from San Francisco to  Chicago starts at $179 from Thu, Aug 7 to Wed, Aug 13. The cheapest one-way flight starts at $90 and departs on Tue, Aug 12.When should you visit Chicago?Chicago\'s peak season is Jun–Aug. Popular events throughout year include St. Patrick\'s Day, when the river is tinted green (Mar 17); the Pride Parade (Jun); the Taste of Chicago culinary festival (Jul) and the Jazz Festival (Sep). During the holiday season (Nov–Dec), the Magnificent Mile Lights Festival and Christkindlmarket, a German Christmas market in Daley Plaza, draw crowds to the city.How do I find cheap dates to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?It\'s easy to use Google Flights to find the cheapest days to fly from San Francisco to Chicago.Just click the Departure label near the top of the page to open the calendar. Choose a start date and a return date to see how the round-trip fare changes on those specific days. Adjust the trip type to see one-way fares. The cheapest available flights are highlighted and easy to spot. Once you settle on dates, click the Search button to see flight options and book the deal.You can also turn on price tracking to get alerts if the price changes for a route or flight.Search more flightsPopular trips from San FranciscoClose dialogThese suggestions are based on the cheapest fares to popular destinations in the next six months.Prices include required taxes + fees for 1 adult. Optional charges and bag fees may apply.Vancouver$116Jun 23 — Jul 1Nonstop2 hr 25 minFlair AirlinesTokyo$583Aug 