ring public holidays, school breaks and major local events.Which airlines fly direct from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX)?You can catch a nonstop flight from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX) with 6 carriers, including:\nUnited AirlinesAlaska AirlinesDelta Air LinesAmerican AirlinesSouthwest Airlines\nWhat is the cheapest airline that flies from SFO to LAX?At the moment, the cheapest airline operating one-way flights from SFO to LAX is Southwest Airlines. You can jet off on this route from $37. This fare is based on the lowest price found on Expedia departing within the next three months. The flight takes off from SFO on August 27 2025. Prices were last updated on June 7 2025 and have not changed since.How many flights per day from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX)?When departing from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO), you’ll have your pick from an average of 31 daily direct flights to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX).What are the most popular departure times for flights from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX)?Flights between SFO and LAX are busiest at 7 PM. If you’d like a more relaxed experience and potentially cheaper tickets, choose a time outside the usual busy windows.What day of the week has the most flights from SFO to LAX?If you depart on a Sunday, you’ll get the biggest range of options for flights from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX).What is the earliest flight from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX)?The first flight of the day taking off from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) is at around 6:00AM UTC-8. Board this flight and you’ll land at Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX) at approximately 7:33AM UTC-8. The total flight duration is 1h 33m.How long does it take to fly from San Francisco Intl. Airport (SFO) to Los Angeles Intl. Airport (LAX)?Flights fr